===2000 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of {{Template parameter value|Roper, North Carolina|Infobox settlement||population_as_of}}, there were {{Template parameter value|Roper, North Carolina|Infobox settlement||population_total}} people, 238 households, residing in the town. The [[population density]] was 566.59 people per square mile ({{Template parameter value|Roper, North Carolina|Infobox settlement||population_density_km2}} people per km{{sup|2}}). There were 268 housing units at an average density of {{convert|309.0|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 14.78% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 78.95% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 4.25% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.82% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.82% of the population.

There were 238 households, of which 31.9% had [[child]]ren under the age of 18 living with them, 37.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 28.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 30.3% were not families. About 29.4% of all households were made up of individuals, and 17.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.58 and the average family size was 3.16.

In the town, the population was distributed as 35.4% under the age of 19, 3.1% from 20 to 24, 22.2% from 25 to 44, 21.6% from 45 to 64, and 17.7% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 37.4 years. For every 100 females, there were 75.6 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $19,536, and the median income for a family was $29,457. About 52.2% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 72.1% of those under age 18 and 6.1% of those age 65 or over.<ref name="urlExplore Census Data">{{cite web |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Roper_town,_North_Carolina?g=160XX00US3757740 |title=Explore Census Data |accessdate=March 26, 2023}}</ref>{{clear left}}

